    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. but i've noticed a lot of people say that the \"critical lens\" stuff actually teaches kids that the country is fundamentally broken or something. do you think those concerns about being too biased are valid, or is that just an excuse to avoid talking about the uncomfortable parts of history?",
